{"video_id": "hd4IJZQfiIQ", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.16.16 | 18-01-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hd4IJZQfiIQ", "duration": 1001, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 3.48, "text": " Om Agyana Timiran Dhasya Gyanan Janishalakaya"}, {"start": 3.48, "end": 7.5200000000000005, "text": " Chakshuran Militam Yena Tasmait Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 7.5200000000000005, "end": 11.46, "text": " Nama Om Vishnu Padaya Krishna Preshtaya Bhutale"}, {"start": 11.46, "end": 15.3, "text": " Shri Mate Bhakti Vedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 15.3, "end": 19.5, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine"}, {"start": 19.5, "end": 23.46, "text": " Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pachatya Deshatarine"}, {"start": 23.46, "end": 27.3, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nityananda"}, {"start": 27.3, "end": 31.86, "text": " Shri Advaita Gadadhara Shri Vasadi Gaurabhakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 31.86, "end": 36.02, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare"}, {"start": 36.02, "end": 39.7, "text": " Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 39.7, "end": 44.06, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya"}, {"start": 44.06, "end": 47.760000000000005, "text": " Naram Jai Vanarottamam Deveem Saraswateem Vyasam"}, {"start": 47.760000000000005, "end": 49.5, "text": " Tato Jaya Mudhirayet"}, {"start": 49.5, "end": 56.16, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from the 16th verse of the 16th chapter of the 1st canto of Srimad Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 56.82, "end": 57.28, "text": " This is a very important verse."}, {"start": 57.28, "end": 58.06, "text": " It is a very nice verse."}, {"start": 59.06, "end": 62.480000000000004, "text": " Sarathya Parashada Sevana Sakya Dautya"}, {"start": 62.480000000000004, "end": 67.44, "text": " Veerasana Anugamana Stavana Pranaman"}, {"start": 67.44, "end": 72.26, "text": " Snigdheshu Pandushu Jagat Pranathimcha Vishno"}, {"start": 72.26, "end": 76.66, "text": " Bhaktim Karo Tindrapathish Charanara Vinde"}, {"start": 76.66, "end": 79.02000000000001, "text": " Beautiful verse."}, {"start": 79.24000000000001, "end": 80.22, "text": " What is the meaning of this verse?"}, {"start": 81.36, "end": 85.72, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit heard that out of his causeless mercy"}, {"start": 85.72, "end": 87.2, "text": " Lord Krishna,"}, {"start": 87.28, "end": 87.82000000000001, "text": " or Vishnu,"}, {"start": 88.32000000000001, "end": 90.6, "text": " who is universally obeyed,"}, {"start": 91.34, "end": 93.76, "text": " rendered all kinds of service"}, {"start": 93.76, "end": 96.6, "text": " to the malleable sons of Pandu"}, {"start": 96.6, "end": 98.84, "text": " by accepting posts"}, {"start": 98.84, "end": 101.24000000000001, "text": " ranging from chariot driver"}, {"start": 101.24000000000001, "end": 102.26, "text": " to president,"}, {"start": 102.68, "end": 103.26, "text": " to messenger,"}, {"start": 103.86, "end": 104.3, "text": " friend,"}, {"start": 104.84, "end": 105.62, "text": " night watchman,"}, {"start": 105.8, "end": 106.18, "text": " etc."}, {"start": 106.86, "end": 109.06, "text": " according to the will of the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 109.64, "end": 111.24000000000001, "text": " obeying them like a servant"}, {"start": 111.24000000000001, "end": 115.38, "text": " and offering obeisances like one younger in years."}, {"start": 115.38, "end": 118.6, "text": " When Pariksit heard this,"}, {"start": 119.14, "end": 122.5, "text": " he became overwhelmed with devotion"}, {"start": 122.5, "end": 125.61999999999999, "text": " to the lotus feet of the Lord."}, {"start": 128.62, "end": 130.98, "text": " What a beautiful description here."}, {"start": 132.42, "end": 136.56, "text": " So the people were describing glorifying Krishna"}, {"start": 136.56, "end": 139.01999999999998, "text": " that Krishna,"}, {"start": 140.12, "end": 142.42, "text": " even though he is a supreme Lord,"}, {"start": 142.42, "end": 145.26, "text": " he is obeyed universally by everybody,"}, {"start": 145.94, "end": 148.26, "text": " everyone else is a servant."}, {"start": 148.85999999999999, "end": 149.9, "text": " He is the only master."}, {"start": 151.22, "end": 151.51999999999998, "text": " But,"}, {"start": 152.4, "end": 155.6, "text": " because of his affection for his devotees,"}, {"start": 156.16, "end": 157.9, "text": " Krishna agrees to become"}, {"start": 157.9, "end": 160.35999999999999, "text": " a servant of his devotees."}, {"start": 161.96, "end": 165.76, "text": " He is willing to pay obeisances to his devotee"}, {"start": 165.76, "end": 170.48, "text": " even though he is the superior in all circumstances."}, {"start": 170.48, "end": 173.2, "text": " He is the supreme in all circumstances."}, {"start": 174.26, "end": 174.54, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 174.54, "end": 177.1, "text": " Shrila Prabhupada says in the purport,"}, {"start": 177.1, "end": 181.7, "text": " Lord Krishna is everything to the unalloyed devotees"}, {"start": 181.7, "end": 182.66, "text": " like the Pandavas."}, {"start": 182.84, "end": 184.89999999999998, "text": " Unalloyed devotees means pure devotees."}, {"start": 186.23999999999998, "end": 191.95999999999998, "text": " Their bhakti is not mixed with any material contamination."}, {"start": 193.32, "end": 194.98, "text": " What are the material contaminations"}, {"start": 194.98, "end": 198.07999999999998, "text": " in our rendering devotional service?"}, {"start": 198.07999999999998, "end": 202.76, "text": " When somebody performs bhakti for some material benefit,"}, {"start": 204.54, "end": 211.29999999999998, "text": " then such bhakti is called materially contaminated bhakti."}, {"start": 211.29999999999998, "end": 217.07999999999998, "text": " Because bhakti should be rendered"}, {"start": 217.07999999999998, "end": 221.94, "text": " only for the sake of awakening our love for Krishna,"}, {"start": 222.1, "end": 223.78, "text": " awakening our devotion to Krishna,"}, {"start": 223.78, "end": 229.84, "text": " for the sake of becoming purified of all material contamination."}, {"start": 232.06, "end": 234.38, "text": " Not increasing the material contamination,"}, {"start": 234.38, "end": 242.38, "text": " not keeping the material contamination very, very securely."}, {"start": 242.76, "end": 242.94, "text": " No."}, {"start": 244.04, "end": 246.48, "text": " That's not real bhakti."}, {"start": 247.5, "end": 249.76, "text": " Though sometimes that also is called bhakti."}, {"start": 250.48, "end": 251.9, "text": " When somebody prays to Krishna,"}, {"start": 252.64, "end": 255.46, "text": " I want some wealth"}, {"start": 255.46, "end": 258.98, "text": " or I want some relief from some disease,"}, {"start": 260.7, "end": 263.38, "text": " this is called bhakti."}, {"start": 263.38, "end": 264.26, "text": " Bhakti is called bhakti."}, {"start": 264.26, "end": 264.36, "text": " Bhakti is called bhakti."}, {"start": 264.38, "end": 268.8, "text": " Bhakti which is contaminated by material desires."}, {"start": 270.34, "end": 275.88, "text": " So the Pandavas and many such great devotees"}, {"start": 275.88, "end": 278.02, "text": " described and glorified in the Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 278.02, "end": 281.62, "text": " are all pure devotees, unalloyed devotees."}, {"start": 282.04, "end": 283.1, "text": " Just like pure gold."}, {"start": 285.18, "end": 286.06, "text": " Pure gold."}, {"start": 286.96, "end": 288.71999999999997, "text": " So unalloyed."}, {"start": 289.06, "end": 291.71999999999997, "text": " That is no mixture of any other metal."}, {"start": 292.3, "end": 292.88, "text": " Pure gold."}, {"start": 292.88, "end": 295.48, "text": " Similarly, pure bhakti."}, {"start": 296.04, "end": 297.44, "text": " Bhakti means pure bhakti."}, {"start": 298.82, "end": 302.88, "text": " Of course, nowadays they have a concept of"}, {"start": 302.88, "end": 305.34, "text": " 18 carat gold"}, {"start": 305.34, "end": 309.36, "text": " or 16 carat gold."}, {"start": 310.6, "end": 312.6, "text": " That means it's not pure gold."}, {"start": 314.0, "end": 317.94, "text": " 16 parts out of 24 are gold."}, {"start": 317.94, "end": 321.0, "text": " So that means 8 parts,"}, {"start": 322.21999999999997, "end": 322.76, "text": " 1,"}, {"start": 322.76, "end": 333.76, "text": " 1 3rd of that ornament is actually some other cheaper metal like copper or some other metal."}, {"start": 333.76, "end": 335.76, "text": " So that's not pure gold."}, {"start": 335.76, "end": 339.76, "text": " So 16 carat gold strictly cannot be called gold."}, {"start": 340.76, "end": 342.76, "text": " When you say gold, we mean pure gold."}, {"start": 342.76, "end": 346.26, "text": " Similarly, when we say bhakti in the scriptures,"}, {"start": 346.26, "end": 349.76, "text": " when it is said bhakti, it means pure devotion."}, {"start": 349.76, "end": 351.76, "text": " 100% devotion to Krishna."}, {"start": 352.76, "end": 354.76, "text": " And what is that 100% devotion?"}, {"start": 354.76, "end": 357.76, "text": " No material desires."}, {"start": 357.76, "end": 359.76, "text": " Free from all material desires."}, {"start": 362.76, "end": 366.76, "text": " So whenever somebody renders devotional service to Krishna,"}, {"start": 368.76, "end": 371.76, "text": " it should be free from any material desires."}, {"start": 371.76, "end": 373.76, "text": " That's called unalloyed devotion."}, {"start": 373.76, "end": 374.76, "text": " Pure devotion."}, {"start": 374.76, "end": 375.76, "text": " Real devotion."}, {"start": 376.76, "end": 380.76, "text": " If there is no material desire or material ambition"}, {"start": 380.76, "end": 383.76, "text": " to be fulfilled while rendering service to Krishna,"}, {"start": 383.76, "end": 386.76, "text": " then why render service at all?"}, {"start": 386.76, "end": 393.76, "text": " So there is a certain particular purpose in rendering devotional service to Krishna"}, {"start": 393.76, "end": 396.76, "text": " and that is only for one purpose."}, {"start": 396.76, "end": 400.76, "text": " Simply to please Krishna by one's service."}, {"start": 400.76, "end": 402.76, "text": " That's all."}, {"start": 402.76, "end": 406.76, "text": " So all pure devotees render service to Krishna"}, {"start": 406.76, "end": 409.76, "text": " only to please him and for no other purpose."}, {"start": 409.76, "end": 412.76, "text": " For no other purpose."}, {"start": 414.76, "end": 418.76, "text": " So the Pandavas, they are pure devotees."}, {"start": 418.76, "end": 421.76, "text": " They render service to Krishna"}, {"start": 421.76, "end": 424.76, "text": " simply for the sake of pleasing Krishna."}, {"start": 425.76, "end": 430.76, "text": " So for the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 431.76, "end": 434.76, "text": " Krishna was the supreme lord,"}, {"start": 434.76, "end": 436.76, "text": " the spiritual master,"}, {"start": 436.76, "end": 438.76, "text": " the worshipable deity,"}, {"start": 438.76, "end": 439.76, "text": " the guide,"}, {"start": 439.76, "end": 441.76, "text": " the chariot driver,"}, {"start": 441.76, "end": 442.76, "text": " the friend,"}, {"start": 442.76, "end": 443.76, "text": " the servant,"}, {"start": 443.76, "end": 445.76, "text": " the messenger,"}, {"start": 445.76, "end": 448.76, "text": " and everything they could conceive of."}, {"start": 451.76, "end": 452.76, "text": " You see."}, {"start": 452.76, "end": 454.76, "text": " Why would the Pandavas make Krishna"}, {"start": 455.76, "end": 457.76, "text": " their chariot driver, Arjuna?"}, {"start": 457.76, "end": 460.76, "text": " Why did he make Krishna his chariot driver?"}, {"start": 462.76, "end": 464.76, "text": " If he has got devotion to Krishna,"}, {"start": 465.76, "end": 466.76, "text": " how can he"}, {"start": 466.76, "end": 469.76, "text": " even think of asking Krishna,"}, {"start": 469.76, "end": 472.76, "text": " can you please be my chariot driver"}, {"start": 472.76, "end": 475.76, "text": " when I fight in the battle?"}, {"start": 475.76, "end": 478.76, "text": " This is because"}, {"start": 478.76, "end": 481.76, "text": " of the intimate relationship"}, {"start": 481.76, "end": 483.76, "text": " between Arjuna and Krishna."}, {"start": 483.76, "end": 486.76, "text": " That's described in the scriptures."}, {"start": 486.76, "end": 489.76, "text": " Intimate relationship."}, {"start": 489.76, "end": 492.76, "text": " In their intimate relationship,"}, {"start": 492.76, "end": 494.76, "text": " devotees forget Krishna"}, {"start": 494.76, "end": 497.76, "text": " is the supreme personality of Godhead."}, {"start": 499.76, "end": 502.76, "text": " And Krishna also likes"}, {"start": 502.76, "end": 505.76, "text": " the devotees"}, {"start": 505.76, "end": 507.76, "text": " reciprocating with him"}, {"start": 507.76, "end": 508.76, "text": " or serving him"}, {"start": 508.76, "end": 510.76, "text": " intimately"}, {"start": 510.76, "end": 514.76, "text": " while not being conscious of Krishna's supreme position."}, {"start": 515.76, "end": 517.76, "text": " Because that supremacy of Krishna"}, {"start": 517.76, "end": 520.76, "text": " comes in the way of their"}, {"start": 520.76, "end": 523.76, "text": " rendering intimate loving service."}, {"start": 524.76, "end": 526.76, "text": " Just like Mother Yashoda."}, {"start": 527.76, "end": 528.76, "text": " If she"}, {"start": 529.76, "end": 532.76, "text": " is conscious that Krishna is the supreme lord,"}, {"start": 532.76, "end": 536.76, "text": " then she cannot show her motherly affection to Krishna."}, {"start": 538.76, "end": 539.76, "text": " If Krishna becomes naughty,"}, {"start": 539.76, "end": 542.76, "text": " Mother Yashoda does not chastise Krishna,"}, {"start": 542.76, "end": 544.76, "text": " then where is motherly affection?"}, {"start": 547.76, "end": 550.76, "text": " Nor can Mother Yashoda actually"}, {"start": 551.76, "end": 553.76, "text": " do any service"}, {"start": 553.76, "end": 557.76, "text": " in terms of her motherly affection?"}, {"start": 557.76, "end": 559.76, "text": " If she knows Krishna is the supreme lord,"}, {"start": 559.76, "end": 562.76, "text": " where is the question of feeding Krishna?"}, {"start": 563.76, "end": 565.76, "text": " If Krishna is the supreme lord,"}, {"start": 565.76, "end": 566.76, "text": " he never becomes hungry,"}, {"start": 566.76, "end": 568.76, "text": " he is never in need of any food."}, {"start": 568.76, "end": 570.76, "text": " He is the one who is supplying everybody."}, {"start": 570.76, "end": 572.76, "text": " He is completely self-satisfied."}, {"start": 572.76, "end": 573.76, "text": " He is full in himself."}, {"start": 573.76, "end": 575.76, "text": " He is not in need of any food."}, {"start": 575.76, "end": 577.76, "text": " He never gets hungry."}, {"start": 578.76, "end": 579.76, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 579.76, "end": 581.76, "text": " the service"}, {"start": 581.76, "end": 584.76, "text": " is simply for the sake of"}, {"start": 584.76, "end": 587.76, "text": " loving reciprocation between the lord and his pure devotees."}, {"start": 587.76, "end": 589.76, "text": " This should be understood."}, {"start": 592.76, "end": 593.76, "text": " Now,"}, {"start": 593.76, "end": 596.76, "text": " when the devotee renders service to Krishna,"}, {"start": 596.76, "end": 598.76, "text": " to please Krishna,"}, {"start": 598.76, "end": 601.76, "text": " Krishna reciprocates by himself"}, {"start": 601.76, "end": 603.76, "text": " becoming the servant of his devotees,"}, {"start": 603.76, "end": 606.76, "text": " or himself rendering service to the devotees,"}, {"start": 606.76, "end": 609.76, "text": " again to please the devotees."}, {"start": 609.76, "end": 613.76, "text": " Just like devotees want to please Krishna"}, {"start": 613.76, "end": 615.76, "text": " by serving Krishna,"}, {"start": 615.76, "end": 619.76, "text": " Krishna wants to please his devotees by serving them."}, {"start": 619.76, "end": 621.76, "text": " Please understand,"}, {"start": 621.76, "end": 625.76, "text": " when scriptures say we are servants of Krishna,"}, {"start": 625.76, "end": 629.76, "text": " the concept of servant of Krishna"}, {"start": 629.76, "end": 633.76, "text": " is not like the concept of servant in the material world."}, {"start": 633.76, "end": 638.76, "text": " Never mistakenly think that servant means servant like in the material world."}, {"start": 638.76, "end": 640.76, "text": " No."}, {"start": 640.76, "end": 642.76, "text": " In the spiritual world,"}, {"start": 645.76, "end": 649.76, "text": " all positions are absolute positions."}, {"start": 649.76, "end": 651.76, "text": " Prabhupada explains this in another place."}, {"start": 652.76, "end": 655.76, "text": " The servant is the master."}, {"start": 655.76, "end": 657.76, "text": " The master is the servant."}, {"start": 657.76, "end": 659.76, "text": " There is no difference."}, {"start": 661.76, "end": 663.76, "text": " What is the meaning of that?"}, {"start": 664.76, "end": 667.76, "text": " Like Krishna demonstrated,"}, {"start": 668.76, "end": 672.76, "text": " before the battle of Kurukshetra,"}, {"start": 672.76, "end": 677.76, "text": " Krishna is the lord,"}, {"start": 677.76, "end": 680.76, "text": " or playing the role of the lord,"}, {"start": 680.76, "end": 683.76, "text": " and Arjuna is playing the role of"}, {"start": 683.76, "end": 687.76, "text": " the subordinate to the lord."}, {"start": 687.76, "end": 690.76, "text": " But on the battlefield of Kurukshetra,"}, {"start": 690.76, "end": 694.76, "text": " Krishna agreed to become the chariot driver of Arjuna,"}, {"start": 694.76, "end": 697.76, "text": " and Arjuna ordered Krishna,"}, {"start": 697.76, "end": 700.76, "text": " please take my chariot between the two armies,"}, {"start": 700.76, "end": 703.76, "text": " so that I can see with whom I have to fight."}, {"start": 710.76, "end": 712.76, "text": " He is ordering Krishna."}, {"start": 712.76, "end": 714.76, "text": " Krishna says, okay,"}, {"start": 714.76, "end": 715.76, "text": " according to your order,"}, {"start": 715.76, "end": 717.76, "text": " I will take the chariot between the two armies."}, {"start": 719.76, "end": 725.76, "text": " So, this is the kind of reciprocation"}, {"start": 725.76, "end": 727.76, "text": " between the lord and his devotees."}, {"start": 729.76, "end": 731.76, "text": " So, Maharaj Pariksit,"}, {"start": 731.76, "end": 733.76, "text": " as a pure devotee of the lord,"}, {"start": 733.76, "end": 735.76, "text": " he could appreciate"}, {"start": 735.76, "end": 737.76, "text": " the lord's transcendental reciprocation"}, {"start": 737.76, "end": 739.76, "text": " of the feelings of his devotees."}, {"start": 739.76, "end": 741.76, "text": " And thus, he himself was also overwhelmed"}, {"start": 741.76, "end": 743.76, "text": " with the dealings of the lord."}, {"start": 743.76, "end": 745.76, "text": " He began to feel"}, {"start": 745.76, "end": 747.76, "text": " Krishna is so kind"}, {"start": 747.76, "end": 749.76, "text": " to his devotees,"}, {"start": 749.76, "end": 751.76, "text": " that he is willing to do anything"}, {"start": 751.76, "end": 753.76, "text": " for his devotee."}, {"start": 753.76, "end": 756.76, "text": " Just like the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 756.76, "end": 759.76, "text": " Krishna acted as a night watchman"}, {"start": 759.76, "end": 760.76, "text": " for the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 760.76, "end": 762.76, "text": " because they were exiled."}, {"start": 762.76, "end": 765.76, "text": " And in the forest,"}, {"start": 765.76, "end": 768.76, "text": " you see, they are not with all their"}, {"start": 768.76, "end": 772.76, "text": " army and the security."}, {"start": 772.76, "end": 774.76, "text": " No."}, {"start": 774.76, "end": 776.76, "text": " They are without that."}, {"start": 776.76, "end": 779.76, "text": " So, if there is danger,"}, {"start": 779.76, "end": 781.76, "text": " what happens?"}, {"start": 781.76, "end": 782.76, "text": " Krishna's devotees."}, {"start": 782.76, "end": 784.76, "text": " So, naturally,"}, {"start": 784.76, "end": 786.76, "text": " when they are in danger as devotees,"}, {"start": 786.76, "end": 787.76, "text": " they think of Krishna."}, {"start": 787.76, "end": 790.76, "text": " And Krishna immediately responds"}, {"start": 790.76, "end": 792.76, "text": " to his devotees."}, {"start": 792.76, "end": 794.76, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 794.76, "end": 796.76, "text": " because Pandavas were in forest,"}, {"start": 796.76, "end": 800.76, "text": " and there was danger at night,"}, {"start": 800.76, "end": 802.76, "text": " Krishna used to be"}, {"start": 802.76, "end": 804.76, "text": " guarding the Pandavas"}, {"start": 804.76, "end": 806.76, "text": " as the night watchman."}, {"start": 808.76, "end": 810.76, "text": " Then they have to take some rest."}, {"start": 810.76, "end": 811.76, "text": " You see,"}, {"start": 811.76, "end": 815.76, "text": " there is a word used here."}, {"start": 815.76, "end": 817.76, "text": " Prabhupad says that"}, {"start": 817.76, "end": 820.76, "text": " in this description"}, {"start": 820.76, "end": 825.76, "text": " of what all Krishna was to the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 825.76, "end": 828.76, "text": " Veera Asana."}, {"start": 828.76, "end": 829.76, "text": " Veera Asana,"}, {"start": 829.76, "end": 832.76, "text": " Krishna accepted the post of Veera Asana means"}, {"start": 832.76, "end": 835.76, "text": " acceptance of the post of a watchman"}, {"start": 835.76, "end": 838.76, "text": " with a drawn sword at night."}, {"start": 838.76, "end": 840.76, "text": " Like he is holding a sword"}, {"start": 840.76, "end": 844.76, "text": " and waiting upon the Pandavas"}, {"start": 844.76, "end": 847.76, "text": " that nobody should harm the Pandavas."}, {"start": 847.76, "end": 850.76, "text": " If somebody comes or attempts to even"}, {"start": 850.76, "end": 852.76, "text": " attack the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 852.76, "end": 854.76, "text": " they are going to be immediately killed"}, {"start": 854.76, "end": 855.76, "text": " with the sword."}, {"start": 855.76, "end": 860.76, "text": " So, that kind of service Krishna accepted"}, {"start": 860.76, "end": 864.76, "text": " out of his affection for the Pandavas."}, {"start": 864.76, "end": 866.76, "text": " Simply because of affection."}, {"start": 866.76, "end": 868.76, "text": " So, in this way,"}, {"start": 868.76, "end": 871.76, "text": " Pariksit heard"}, {"start": 871.76, "end": 874.76, "text": " that the dealings of the Lord"}, {"start": 874.76, "end": 875.76, "text": " and his pure devotees"}, {"start": 875.76, "end": 877.76, "text": " is so very sweet,"}, {"start": 877.76, "end": 879.76, "text": " so very relatable,"}, {"start": 879.76, "end": 883.76, "text": " that Pariksit began to feel himself,"}, {"start": 883.76, "end": 886.76, "text": " his devotion towards Krishna"}, {"start": 886.76, "end": 892.76, "text": " being aroused into ecstasy."}, {"start": 892.76, "end": 893.76, "text": " And out of ecstasy,"}, {"start": 893.76, "end": 897.76, "text": " he began to shed tears of love for Krishna."}, {"start": 898.76, "end": 901.76, "text": " And that is being described here."}, {"start": 901.76, "end": 903.76, "text": " So, Srila Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 903.76, "end": 906.76, "text": " even though the Lord's feelings towards,"}, {"start": 906.76, "end": 907.76, "text": " dealings with his devotees"}, {"start": 907.76, "end": 910.76, "text": " appear to be like ordinary human dealings,"}, {"start": 910.76, "end": 912.76, "text": " but the truth is"}, {"start": 912.76, "end": 916.76, "text": " that they are all completely transcendental."}, {"start": 916.76, "end": 919.76, "text": " They are spiritual reciprocation"}, {"start": 919.76, "end": 921.76, "text": " between Krishna and his pure devotees."}, {"start": 921.76, "end": 925.76, "text": " They have no tinge of any material contamination in them."}, {"start": 925.76, "end": 927.76, "text": " There is no material sentiment."}, {"start": 927.76, "end": 932.76, "text": " That Krishna did this to me,"}, {"start": 932.76, "end": 933.76, "text": " gave me this favour,"}, {"start": 933.76, "end": 936.76, "text": " so now I have to actually do some other favour to Krishna."}, {"start": 936.76, "end": 937.76, "text": " No."}, {"start": 937.76, "end": 939.76, "text": " None of those calculations are there."}, {"start": 939.76, "end": 942.76, "text": " Neither they think,"}, {"start": 942.76, "end": 944.76, "text": " oh, Krishna is powerful,"}, {"start": 944.76, "end": 947.76, "text": " so he is capable of protecting me."}, {"start": 947.76, "end": 949.76, "text": " No."}, {"start": 949.76, "end": 951.76, "text": " No such calculation."}, {"start": 951.76, "end": 953.76, "text": " No such calculation."}, {"start": 953.76, "end": 956.76, "text": " So, there is a distinct difference"}, {"start": 956.76, "end": 959.76, "text": " between Krishna's activities,"}, {"start": 959.76, "end": 962.76, "text": " his dealings with his devotees,"}, {"start": 962.76, "end": 970.76, "text": " his incarnations,"}, {"start": 970.76, "end": 974.76, "text": " and the conditioned souls"}, {"start": 974.76, "end": 977.76, "text": " performing some activities"}, {"start": 977.76, "end": 980.76, "text": " or relating with other conditioned souls."}, {"start": 980.76, "end": 983.76, "text": " There is a lot of difference between the two."}, {"start": 983.76, "end": 984.76, "text": " So, therefore,"}, {"start": 984.76, "end": 986.76, "text": " hearing about Krishna's activities"}, {"start": 986.76, "end": 989.76, "text": " itself is devotional service."}, {"start": 989.76, "end": 992.76, "text": " It is completely a transcendental activity."}, {"start": 992.76, "end": 993.76, "text": " And it purifies us"}, {"start": 993.76, "end": 995.76, "text": " and makes us eligible to go back,"}, {"start": 995.76, "end": 996.76, "text": " come back to God."}, {"start": 996.76, "end": 997.76, "text": " So, I will stop here."}, {"start": 997.76, "end": 998.76, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 998.76, "end": 999.76, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}